      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(sessions-files): exclude workspace-external files from workspace rail list",
        "body": "Fixes #95685\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\nThe Session Workspace Rail (right sidebar, added in 2026.6.9) marks files outside the configured workspace directory as \"missing\" (red badge), even though those files exist and were successfully read during the session. This is confusing because users see alarming red markers for files that are perfectly fine.\n\n## Evidence\n\n### Fix\n\nIn `buildListResult()`, filter out files outside the configured workspace directory before returning the file list. Uses the existing `resolveTouchedFilePath()` to determine whether a file path resolves inside the workspace root.\n\n- Files inside the workspace that genuinely don't exist on disk still show as `missing: true`\n- Files outside the workspace (e.g. system lib paths) are excluded from the list\n- The browser explorer view is unaffected\n\n### Verification\n\n```\n✅ OK\n```\n\n### What was not tested\n\nEnd-to-end with real gateway Control UI. Logic follows the same path check used by other session file operations.\n\n## Changes\n\n1 file, +17/-2. Lockfile unchanged. Rebased to latest origin/main.\n",
